<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="FO3" checkit-title="Substitution for First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Use an appropriate substitution
      to show that all of the following ODEs may be transformed into
      the same linear ODE.
      (Do not fully solve these ODEs.)
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><m>-5 \, t^{4} + 7 \, {y'} = -18 \, t^{9} - 21 \, t^{8} y - 6</m></li>
        <li><m>5 \, t^{6} + y = 3 \, t^{9} y + t {y'}</m></li>
        <li><m>5 \, t^{4} y^{6} + 5 \, {y'} = 3 \, t^{8} y</m></li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = 6 \, t + 7 \, y</m>.</p></li>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = \frac{y}{t}</m>.</p></li>
            <li><p>Let <m>u = \frac{1}{y^{5}}</m>.</p></li>
    </ol>
      <p>
          All ODEs transform into
          <m>3 \, t^{8} u + {u'} = 5 \, t^{4}</m>.
      </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
